{
  "stem": "4963.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they were really, in thinking back, I-- I really cannot imagine how-- how wonderful, humanitarian people they were to risk their lives and their children's lives to hide a Jewish child, you know, was really incredible when I think about it.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, I was there for about six months and in 19-- in June 1944 the Russians were back in Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And these people would tell me about the fires that they saw, ghetto, that the ghetto was being-- the people were liquidated, that they were-- they were sent out, they were taken by trains to Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, to-- to Stutthof and Dachau-- and Dachau, Poland and Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My-- my whole family, was-- my aunts and uncles, they were all-- they all left the ghetto by trains, you know, and separated into Stutthof.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now my Aunt Chassia--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I lived there for six months.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they-- as I said, they were really very nice to me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was frightened-- no, I was only frightened in incidences where-- where I heard shootings.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I could see the Germans going around into-- into the streets with loudspeakers, announcing that anyone who is going to-- who is hiding a Jewish child-- you know, or Jewish people-- would be shot.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I can remember shootings.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, I can remember gunshots.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I would not look out the window, because, again, you know, I was-- they had curtains and I wasn't-- I was forbidden to-- to go near a window.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had-- these people had a-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] think it was a lady's [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] brother who was there.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
